    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"joy in the journey\" is such a hollow concept when the journey itself is just suffering and repetition. if the end result is always the same—total oblivion—then why bother forcing yourself to carry the weight of being? it feels more like a trap than a journey. doesn't it make more sense that if nothing matters, then the struggle to keep going is also just an unnecessary burden?",
